{{Use British English|date=April 2018}}{{Infobox model | name = Nicola Tappenden | image = Nicola Tappenden.jpg | caption = Tappenden outside ''[[Wags Boutique]]'', April 2007 | birth_name = | birth_date = 1982 | birth_place = [[London Borough of Croydon|Croydon]], [[Surrey]], England | children = | spouse = | occupation = [[Model (people)|Model]] | height = | haircolour = | website = }}
'''Nicola Tappenden''' (born 1982) is an English model. She is also known for appearing in the 2010 edition of ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 7|Celebrity Big Brother]]''. She was the sixth contestant evicted, in a secret eviction, on 27 January 2010. Tappenden is also known by her modelling name '''Nicola T'''.
==Early life and career== Tappenden was born in [[London Borough of Croydon|Croydon]], [[Surrey]].<ref>http://search.findmypast.co.uk/results/world-records/england-and-wales-births-1837-2006?firstname=nicola&lastname=tappenden&eventyear=1982&eventyear_offset=0</ref> She went to [[Shirley High School]] in Croydon.<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/big-brother/6928232/Celebrity-Big-Brother-profile-of-all-2010-contestants.html</ref> She began her [[Toplessness|topless]] [[Model (people)|modelling]] career as a Page Three girl at the age of 20 in 2002 after winning [[The Sun (United Kingdom)|''The Sun'']]'s first ever Page 3 Idol competition<ref name="yourlocal" /> whilst working for [[Citigroup]] asset management. She has become a regular fixture since, as well as undertaking other glamour and retail [[fashion model]]ling assignments.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}
In May 2007, she entered the [[Miss Great Britain]] contest as Miss Croydon along with [[Michelle Marsh]] as Miss Oldham.<ref>{{Cite news |date = 2007-05-21 |title = Miss Great Britain: The Wag Factor |url = http://www.theinsider.com/news/184122_Miss_Great_Britain_The_Wag_Factor |accessdate = 2010-01-04 }}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Tappenden came in 10th place, with Marsh reaching 4th place.<ref name="yourlocal">{{Cite news|date=2007-05-21|author=Helen Husbands | title= Croydon Beauty In Battle For Miss Great Britain Crown | url= http://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/1414875.croydon_beauty_in_battle_for_miss_great_britain_crown/ | work=yourlocalguardian.co.uk | archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.yourlocalguardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1414875.croydon_beauty_in_battle_for_miss_great_britain_crown%2F&date=2010-01-04 | archivedate= 2010-01-04 | accessdate= 2010-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|year=2007|title=Final '07: Contestants in final place order|url=http://www.miss-gb.co.uk/contestants.asp?view=place|publisher=Miss Great Britain|accessdate=2010-01-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090218130126/http://miss-gb.co.uk/contestants.asp?view=place|archivedate=18 February 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
As an actress, Tappenden appeared in the film ''[[Deuce Bigalow: European Gigolo]]'' in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0367652/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast |title=''Deuce Bigalow: European Gigolo''|date=12 August 2005|accessdate=1 June 2016|via=IMDb}}</ref>
Tappenden was invited to take part in ''[[WAGs Boutique]]'' (due to her relationship with [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] striker [[Bobby Zamora]]), where two teams of [[WAGs]] competed to run two fashion boutiques over a three-month period. Later, in 2007, she released an exercise video, ''WAGS Workout''.<ref>[https://www.amazon.co.uk/WAGS-Workout-DVD/dp/B000WZJH34 WAGS Workout 2007 DVD], Released: 2007-12-24, Runtime: 117 minutes<!-- # ASIN: B000WZJH34 --></ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2007-12-11|title=Look like a WAG this Christmas| url= http://www.metro.co.uk/sport/oddballs/79321-look-like-a-wag-this-christmas |accessdate=2010-01-03}}</ref>
In January 2010, Tappenden was a housemate in the seventh ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 2010 (UK)|Celebrity Big Brother]]''. She was evicted from the reality show on 27 January in a surprise eviction, finishing in 6th place.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/bigbrother/news/a199765/nicola-evicted.html |title=Nicola Evicted!|author=Sarah Rollo|date=27 January 2010|work=Digital Spy|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
She also appeared in ''50 Greatest Plastic Surgery Shockers'' in December 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1799082/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast |title=''50 Greatest Plastic Surgery Shockers''|date=4 December 2010|accessdate=1 June 2016|via=IMDb}}</ref>
Tappenden has recorded a single, called "Drunk", with rapper [[Coolio]], which was released on 1 March 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/coolio/status/8196426973 |title=Coolio on Twitter|work=Twitter|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
She also took part in the [[Race for Life]] single "[[Girls Just Wanna Have Fun]]", which was released in April 2010. The track features several other celebs, including [[Kym Marsh]], [[Danielle Lloyd]], [[Lisa Scott Lee]], and Kelly from [[Liberty X]].{{fact|date=September 2017}}
She also took part in a WAGs edition of ''[[Come Dine with Me]]''.
